{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778247802,"nonce":"AzV2iyzCqAgTEmyXi/6f5j6sDWE=","message":"**Cross-cutting: empirical Δv on flavor-B-trained controllers is negative; analytical Δv on corrected (full-state $B_w$) Riccati is positive.**\n\nEmpirical peak-forward-velocity Δv measured on 45 `LinearDynamicsAdversary`-trained replicates (3 η_max × 3 seeds × 5 reps), single canonical reach, no test-time perturbation, vs `baseline_standard_12k` GRU baseline. Per-η_max mean Δv: −20.75% / −26.40% / −25.68% (η_max = 0.03 / 0.10 / 0.30). Within-condition SD ~40%; replicate-level distribution is **bimodal** (~20–27% of reps at +40 to +57%, rest at −12 to −73%). See `c723082` comment for table; full doc at `results/part2_5/peak_velocity_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md`.\n\nOn the *same* rlrmp regime, the corrected H∞ Riccati (full-state $B_w$, `feature/cs-faithful-riccati-investigation` SHA `0c160e9`) predicts analytical Δv \u003e 0 (synthesis §4.2-revised, §7.2 update). The two findings disagree in *sign* at the group mean.\n\n**Joint reading.** Flavor-B training (PGD over Frobenius-bounded ΔA) is **not** producing C\u0026S-style robust H∞ controllers — it is producing something else. The (a)/(b) framing is no longer load-bearing here: the C\u0026S Δv signature is reachable analytically *without* flavor-(b) (just full-state $B_w$ within flavor-(a)), and the flavor-B training pipeline does not reach it empirically. The new central question is the training-vs-analytical mismatch, not the (a)/(b) distinction.\n\nCross-refs: `c723082` (LinearDynamicsAdversary, this run), `97c227a` (Riccati $B_w$ fix), synthesis doc §7.1.1 / §8.0 (in-flight on `feature/cs-dv-investigation-integration`).","files":null}]}